-- FACTBOX: Dow posts third-worst year ever in 2008
-- 
-- Wed Dec 31, 2008 10:03pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/01/01/us-usa-stocks-dow-ranking-factbox-idUSTRE4BU4LV20090101

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - The Dow Jones Industrial Average finished 2008 down 33.8 percent, marking its third-worst year in history. 

 Below is a list of the ten worst years for the index. Year Pct Change 1931 -52.67 1907 -37.73 2008 -33.84 1930 -33.77 1920 -32.90 1937 -32.82 1914 -30.72 1974 -27.57 1903 -23.61 1932 -23.07 *The stock exchange was closed from July 30, 1914 until December 12, 1914 at the beginning of World War I; from March 3, 1933 until March 15, 1933 due to a mandatory closing of all banks issued by Franklin D. Roosevelt, and from September 10 until September 17, 2001 due to the Sept 11 attack on the World Trade Center. Source: Dow Jones (Reporting by  Rodrigo Campos , Editing by Chizu Nomiyama)